data.title: Seychelles population 2024
data.meta_description:
Year wise population of Seychelles from 1950 to 2100 by United Nations. Data tables and
charts.
data.text:
The current population of Seychelles is 130,817 as of August 30, 2024, based on interpolation of the latest United Nations data. The population of Seychelles is projected at 108,263, or 108k, as of July 1, 2024. The total population in Seychelles is projected at 107,660, or 108k people for the year 2023.

Seychelles ranks 198th in the world by population on the 237 countries and territories list. Seychelles is ranked 57th among 58 countries and territories in Africa.
